{
  "bookId": "laozi-wangbi-wiki",
  "num": 61,
  "title": "第六十一章",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "大國者下流，"
    },
    {
      "text": "天下之交。"
    },
    {
      "text": "天下之牝，"
    },
    {
      "text": "牝常以靜勝牡，以靜為下。"
    },
    {
      "text": "故大國以下小國，"
    },
    {
      "text": "則取小國；"
    },
    {
      "text": "小國以下大國，則取大國。"
    },
    {
      "text": "故或下以取，或下而取。"
    },
    {
      "text": "大國不過欲兼畜人，小國不過欲入事人。夫兩者各得其所欲，大者宜為下。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "江海居大而處下，則百川流之，大國居大而處下，則天下流之，故曰，大國下流也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "天下所歸會也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "靜而不求，物自歸之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 12
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以其靜故能為下也。牝，雌也。雄躁動貪欲，雌常以靜，故能勝雄也。以其靜復能為下，故物歸之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大國以下，猶云以大國下小國。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "小國則附之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 12
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大國納之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言唯修卑下，然後乃各得其所。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 8,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 33
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "小國修下自全而已，不能令天下歸之，大國修下則天下歸之。故曰，各得其所欲，則大者宜為下也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
